<h1>Problem 1650 - 2023 Grossman MO, P7 of 7, GC</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>The plane is colored with two colors so that the following property holds: for each real \(a>0\) there is an equilateral triangle in the plane of side length \(a\) whose \(3\) vertices are of the same color.</p>
<p>Prove that for any three numbers \(a,b,c>0\) for which the sum of any two is greater than the third there is a triangle in the plane with sides \(a\), \(b\), and \(c\) whose \(3\) vertices are of the same color.</p>
